==English==
[[Category:English proper nouns]]

===Etymology===
From Modified Latin ''Americanus'' (''America'' from Latinized name of [[Category:English eponyms]] ''Amerigo'' Vespucci, Italian navigator of 1512).

===Pronunciation===
'''American''' ''([[noun]] and [[adjective]])''
:US: {{SAMPA|/@"mEr@k@n/}}, {{IPA|/ə'mɛrəkən/}}

Anything to do with Steven Colbert

===Proper adjective===
'''American'''

# Of or pertaining to the [[United States of America]], or [[w:Culture of the United States|American culture]]
# Of or pertaining to the [[America]]s. More often this is specified as either "North American" or "South American."

